summary:
Bachelor degree in Tourism, Master degree in Environmental Management, and Ph.D. in Ecology.
Passionate for Antarctica and conservation. Since 2005 contributing to the planning of protected areas, particularly interested in tourism and public use management. Involved in the development of tourism options as a tool for conservation and generation of economic benefits for communities related to protected and natural spaces. Participating in Antarctica expeditions since 2011 and now working to expand my research on the social and environmental dimensions of Antarctic tourism.
